modules.description: Converts OCaml bytecode into JavaScript, enabling execution in web browsers and Node.js. Handles OCaml's native data types and integrates with browser APIs through generated bindings. Supports embedding OCaml logic into web applications without modifying existing OCaml code.

Converts OCaml types to and from JSON representations using custom syntax extensions. Operates on type definitions and annotations to generate serialization and deserialization functions. Enables direct integration of JSON handling in code through compiler plugins.
